Phase: Initial package extraction
Status: IN_PROGRESS

# Next Steps
1. [x] Analyze `grengo/` to map existing functions to `api`, `services`, and `repo` layers.
2. [x] Create directories `internal/api`, `internal/services`, and `internal/repo`.
3. [x] Begin extracting configuration and file-system paths to the `repo` layer.
4. [x] Move HTTP handler implementations under `internal` while keeping router construction in `main`.
5. [ ] Continue moving orchestration beyond self-command execution into narrower `internal/services` packages.
6. [ ] Replace remaining app-level direct filesystem helpers with `internal/repo` methods where practical.
7. [x] Move command implementations out of remaining root flat files into focused internal packages.

# Progress
- Added `grengo/internal/repo` with project-root/path helpers, site env read/write helpers, and arm/disarm filesystem operations.
- Added `grengo/internal/services` with a `CommandRunner` for `grengo` self-command execution used by sync and async API command paths.
- Added `grengo/internal/api` JSON response helpers and routed root API response wrappers through them.
- Updated existing root handlers to use the new packages while preserving current exported command/handler names for this first buildable slice.
- Moved API mux registration, `/health`, and passcode middleware back into `main`/`api.go` per project direction; `internal/api` now only holds reusable response helpers.
- Moved CLI command dispatch into `grengo/internal/cli`; root `main.go` now wires callbacks into the internal CLI runner.
- Split each top-level CLI command entry into a flat `grengo/internal/cli/<command>.go` file; `cli.go` is now the command registry and dispatcher.
- Moved export output-flag parsing out of shared helpers and into the export command entry file where it is used.
- Moved `.pcode` path ownership into `grengo/internal/repo` and routed root passcode path lookup through it.
- Moved all former root command/service/API implementation files into `grengo/internal/app`; `grengo/` now has only `main.go` and `router.go`.
- Added `grengo/router.go` so route registration, `/health`, and passcode middleware remain in the root main package while using handler callbacks from `internal/app`.
- Added `app.CLICommands()` and `app.ConfigureAPIHandler()` so root wiring stays explicit and internal app logic remains tucked away.
- Added `grengo rebuilt frontend [<name>|all]` / `grengo rebuild frontend [<name>|all]` to run the frontend build once and hot-copy `dist` into running backend containers without restarting them.

# Verification
- `env GOCACHE=/tmp/skaia-go-cache GOTMPDIR=/tmp go build -o /tmp/grengo-check .` from `grengo/` passes.
- `env GOCACHE=/tmp/skaia-go-cache GOTMPDIR=/tmp go test ./...` from `grengo/` passes.
- `env GOCACHE=/tmp/skaia-go-cache GOTMPDIR=/tmp go run . help` from `grengo/` shows the new `rebuilt frontend` command.
- `mise exec node@24.16.0 -- npm run build` from `backend/frontend/` passes.

# Notes
- A plain `go build .` attempted to use the sandboxed `~/.cache/go-build` and failed with a read-only cache error, so verification used writable Go cache/temp directories under `/tmp`.
- Existing unrelated deletions remain in the worktree: `.todo/grengo_cli_improvements` and `.todo/grengo_cli_improvements.tip`.
- `go build .` creates an untracked `grengo/grengo` binary; cleanup was not approved previously, so follow-up build verification now uses `-o /tmp/grengo-check`.
- `backend/internal/grengo/handler.go` is modified in the worktree but was not changed as part of this refactor pass.
- Plain `npm run build` currently fails in this workspace because the `mise` npm shim has no project Node version selected; verification used the installed `node@24.16.0` through `mise exec`.
- 2026-06-20: Fixed critical Frappe deployment bug: `frappe.go` `cmdFrappeProvision` was calling `runner.RunSelf("docker", ...)` which ran `grengo docker ...` instead of the Docker binary. Fixed to use `exec.Command("docker", "compose", ...)` directly.
- 2026-06-20: Fixed `dbExists` SQL injection with `sanitizeDBName()` helper in `docker.go`.
- 2026-06-20: Build verified: `env GOCACHE=/tmp/skaia-go-cache GOTMPDIR=/tmp go build ./...` from both `grengo/` and `backend/` passes. All backend tests pass.
